-- Three Russian Climbers Found Dead in Georgian Mountains, TV Says
-- B y   H e l e n a   B e d w e l l
-- 2013-01-11T15:28:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-11/three-russian-climbers-found-dead-in-georgian-mountains-tv-says.html
Three Russian mountain climbers were
found dead on one of the highest peaks in the Caucasus mountains
today after an avalanche, broadcaster Rustavi-2 reported.  The three bodies were brought to the capital, Tbilisi,
today from the Kazbegi region, according to Rustavi-2. A fourth
climber, a teenager, was discovered yesterday and is being
treated for unspecified injuries at a local hospital.  The four climbers began their ascent to Mkinvartsveri, also
known as Kazbegi Mountain, at about 5,047 meters (16,558 feet),
on Jan. 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helena Bedwell in Tbilisi at 
